    <preface>
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>
            <emphasis>Conventions</emphasis> is an integrator framework of Java EE technologies with the objective
            to easy the development of enterprise web applications. The framework leverages 
            other frameworks such as 
            <emphasis>Hibernate</emphasis>, 
            <emphasis>Primefaces</emphasis> and 
            <emphasis>CODI</emphasis> to delivery solutions to 
            common problems like cruding, exception handling, true pagination, UI components, 
            internationalization, annotated queries, security etc... 
        </para>
        <para>
            This guide is divided into a getting started to setup the framework plus four parts, the first one walks through the framework architecture(<xref linkend="part1"/>), the second part shows general utility components(<xref linkend="part2"/>), 
            the third part is dedicated to examples(<xref linkend="part3"/>) and finaly the last part is reserved to 
            <emphasis>Conventions Scaffolding</emphasis> a code generation tool for 
            <emphasis>Conventions</emphasis> based on JBoss Forge(<xref linkend="part4"/>). 
        </para>
    </preface>
   
